  "prompt": "How was the Alioth star named?",
  "response": "The star Alioth, also known as Epsilon Ursae Majoris, received its name from Arabic origins. The name \"Alioth\" is derived from the Arabic word \"aly\u0101t,\" which means \"tail\" or \"fat tail of a sheep.\" This name is part of a tradition where many stars have names that come from Arabic based on ancient astronomers' observations and descriptions. Alioth is one of the brightest stars in the constellation Ursa Major and is specifically part of the asterism known as the Big Dipper, where it represents the flanks or tail of the bear figure.",
